=== Usage ===

*This template can be used to display a status indicator along the top of your user page and/or user talk page. 
*It accepts five parameters that should be placed in [[Special:MyPage/Status]]: online, busy, around, offline, sleep
*It is compatible with the [[User:TheDJ/Qui|Qui]] status system developed by [[User:TheDJ|TheDJ]]
*You can also import (or copy) [[User:Xenocidic/statusChanger2.js]] (or just manually update your status)
*Will only work in the user/user talk namespaces.


;By default, the output will be as follows:
*Status: <span style="color: green; font:bold;">'''Online'''</span> [[File:Ledgreen.png|20px|link=]] - online
*Status: <span style="color: orange; font:bold;">'''Busy'''</span> [[File:Ledorange.png|20px|link=]] - busy
*Status: <span style="color: blue; font:bold;">'''Around'''</span> [[File:Ledblue.png|20px|link=]] - around
*Status: <span style="color: blue; font:bold;">'''Custom'''</span> [[File:Ledblue.png|20px|link=]] - custom. (if sleep= is defined)
*Status: <span style= "color:red;text-decoration:blink">'''Offline'''</span> [[File:Nuvola apps krec.svg|20px|link=]] - offline
*Status: <span style= "color:red;text-decoration:blink">'''Sleeping'''</span> [[File:Nuvola apps krec.svg|20px|link=]] - sleep (default)
*Status: <span style="color: gray; font:bold;text-decoration:blink;">'''Unknown'''</span> [[File:Ledgray.png|20px|link=]] - if your status is not being reported correctly


;The first parameter is optional and may be used to point to a status page other than [[Special:MyPage/Status]]


;Can also accept named parameters
*'''link''': can be used to link the text to a page which explains the status terms (e.g. [[User talk:Xenocidic/Status]])
*'''img_link''': can be used to link the status image (e.g. [[User talk:Xenocidic/Status]])
*'''offset''': can be used to offset the status display further to the left
*'''offsettop''': can be used to offset further down
*'''sleep''': redefine the "sleep" parameter to anything you like
*'''blink''': will prevent flashing in "offline" and "sleep" status when set to any value (such as "no")
*'''nocat''': to remove a user from the category when they are online (see [[#Wikipedians online|below]])


;Example usage:
*<code><nowiki>{{Statustop|offset=30}}</nowiki></code>
*:&ndash; the offset parameter is in px units
*<code><nowiki>{{Statustop|link=User talk:Xenocidic/Status|offset=500}}</nowiki></code>
*:&ndash; the default is to leave the text and image unlinked
*<code><nowiki>{{Statustop|link=User talk:Xenocidic/Status|img_link=Template:Statustop|offset=10}}</nowiki></code>
*:&ndash; the img_link parameter accepts both wikipages and external URLs
*<code><nowiki>{{Statustop|User:SomeOtherUser/Status}}</nowiki></code>
*:&ndash; could be used on a bot page to display the bot-op's status.
*<code><nowiki>{{Statustop|sleep=IRC}}</nowiki></code> - for setting the custom parameter